'''Birgit Aagard-Svendsen''' (born 1956) is a Danish [[business executive]] who as of September 2015, became the executive vice-president and [[chief financial officer]] of the [[J. Lauritzen A/S|J. Lauritzen]] shipping company in [[Copenhagen]], Denmark.<ref name=kvinfo>{{cite web|url=http://www.kvinfo.dk/side/634/action/2/vis/1150/|title=Birgit Aagard-Svendsen|publisher=Kvinfo|accessdate=7 September 2015 |language=Danish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.j-l.com/copenhagen-office|title=Copenhagen office|publisher=J. Lauritzen A/S|accessdate=7 September 2015 |language=Danish}}</ref>
Aagard-Svendsen graduated in engineering from [[Technical University of Denmark|Danmarks Ingeniørakademi]] (1980) and in business administration at Copenhagen's [[Copenhagen Business School|Handelshøjskolen]] (1985). Before joining J. Lauritzen in 1998, she held management positions at [[TDC A/S|Tele Danmark]] (1996–98) and [[Nordisk Film]] (1996–98).<ref name=kvinfo/> She has previously been chairman of the Infrastructure Commission and also headed the Committee on Corporate Governance.<ref name= top>{{citenews | url=http://www.altinget.dk/navnenyt/topleder-forlader-rederiet-j-lauritzen | title= Top manager leaves the shipping company J.Lauritzen | newspaper= Altinge | date= February 25, 2016 | accessdate= March 3, 2017}}</ref>
Aagard-Svendsen is married to {{Interlanguage link multi|Rolf Aagaard-Svendsen|da}}, a former mayor of [[Lyngby-Taarbæk]], and has two daughters. In 2008, she was named businesswoman of the year by the Danish newspaper ''[[Berlingske]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.business.dk/karriere/aarets-erhvervskvinde-direktoer-birgit-aagaard-svendsen|title=Årets erhvervskvinde: Direktør Birgit Aagaard-Svendsen |publisher=''Berlingske''|date=14 April 2008|accessdate=7 September 2015 |language=Danish}}</ref>
