{{Orphan|date=February 2017}}
{{Infobox person | name = Hussain Saeed Alnahdi | image = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = {{birth based on age as of date|24|2016|10|31|noage=1|df=y}} | birth_place = | death_date = {{Death date|2016|10|31|df=y}} (age 24) | death_place = [[Mayo Clinic]], [[Eau Claire, Wisconsin|Eau Claire]], [[Wisconsin]], [[United States]] | death_cause = Murder | resting_place = | resting_place_coordinates = | monuments = | residence = [[Sharurah]], [[Saudi Arabia]] | nationality = | other_names = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = Student | years_active = | employer = | organization = | style = | home_town = | religion = | spouse = | partner = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = | website = }} '''Hussain Saeed Alnahdi''' was a 24-year-old [[University of Wisconsin–Stout]] student from [[Sharurah]], [[Saudi Arabia]], majoring in Business Administration, who was murdered in [[Menomonie, Wisconsin|Menomonie]], in [[Dunn County, Wisconsin|Dunn County]], Wisconsin, United States, in 2016.<ref name="Garza">{{Cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2016/11/01/saudi-student-assaulted-wisconsin-dies-his-injuries/93101338/ |title=Saudi student is beaten, killed in Wisconsin |first1=Jesse |last1=Garza |first2=Karen |last2=Herzog |work=[[USA Today]] |date=1 November 2016 |accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref><ref name="Hawkins">{{Cite web |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2016/11/01/saudi-college-student-in-wisconsin-dies-after-assault/ |title= Saudi college student in Wisconsin dies after assault |work=[[The Washington Post|Washington Post]] |first=Derek |last=Hawkins |date=1 November 2016 |accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref><ref name="Hauser">{{Cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/04/us/killing-of-saudi-university-student-shakes-wisconsin-city.html |title=Killing of Saudi Student Shakes Wisconsin College Town |work=[[The New York Times|New York Times]] |first=Christine |last=Hauser |date=3 November 2016 |accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref><ref name="SameeAli">{{Cite web |url=http://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/saudi-student-s-brutal-killing-shakes-small-wisconsin-town-n677461 |title=A Saudi Student's Brutal Killing Shakes a Small Wisconsin Town |first=Safia |last=Samee Ali |work=[[NBC News]] |date=4 November 2016 |accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref><ref name="Helling">{{Cite web |url=http://people.com/crime/wisconsin-college-saudi-student-saeed-alnahdi-killed/ |title=A Small Town Seeks Answers After Beloved College Student’s Beating Death Outside Pizzeria |first=Steve |last=Helling |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |date=4 November 2016 |accessdate=11 November 2016}}</ref>
Alnahdi was attacked, beaten and left unconscious<ref name="Hawkins" /> outside a pizza restaurant on Main Street East in downtown Menomonie at about 2am on Sunday 30 October 2016.<ref name="Helling" /> He died from his injuries the following day, Monday 31 October,<ref name="Helling" /> at the [[Mayo Clinic]] in [[Eau Claire, Wisconsin|Eau Claire]], having been taken there by helicopter from the Mayo Clinic Health System in Menomonie.<ref name="Hawkins" />
His body was laid to rest on 7 November in [[Sharurah]], Saudi Arabia.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://saudigazette.com.sa/saudi-arabia/sharourah-gov-condoles-alnahdis-father-family/|title=Sharourah Gov. condoles with Alnahdi’s father, family - Saudi Gazette|last=Hussain|first=Sadiq|date=2016-11-07|newspaper=Saudi Gazette|language=en-US|access-date=2016-11-11}}</ref>
A reward of $20,000 has been offered for information leading to the arrest of his killer.<ref name="Hauser" />
On 18 November, police in Menomonie announced that they had identified a suspect for the killing, and that there was no evidence that it was a hate crime.<ref name="Elieff">{{cite web|url=http://www.gomn.com/news/police-have-a-suspect-in-uw-stout-students-death-no-evidence-it-was-a-hate-crime/|title=Police have a suspect in UW-Stout student's death, no evidence it was a hate crime|last=Elieff|first=Josette|date=18 November 2016|work=GoMN|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref> On 22 November, they recommended to the Dunn County district attorney’s office that the suspect be charged with [[Felony murder rule (Wisconsin)|felony murder]] and [[Battery (crime)|substantial battery]].<ref name="SPPP">{{cite web|url=http://www.twincities.com/2016/11/22/police-recommend-murder-charges-in-uw-stout-students-fatal-assault/|title=Felony charges sought in death of Saudi student at U.W.|date=22 November 2016|work=[[St. Paul Pioneer Press]]|accessdate=28 November 2016}}</ref> The suspect, whose name was not given, was said to neither be a student of the University nor a resident of Dunn County.<ref name="Elieff" />
On January 13, 2017, Cullen Osburn was charged with murder of Hussain <ref>http://www.kare11.com/news/mn-man-charged-in-murder-of-uw-stout-student/385795649</ref> and an April 2018 trial has been scheduled <ref>http://chippewa.com/dunnconnect/news/local/trial-date-set-in-uw-stout-student-murder-case/article_71441283-c400-5ca8-b6b0-707553e405a0.html</ref>
The Consulate of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia in Houston has appointed a lawyer to handle all procedural, security, and judicial aspects of this case.<ref name="The Consulate of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia in Houston">{{Cite web |url=http://www.mofa.gov.sa/sites/mofaen/ServicesAndInformation/news/MinistryNews/Pages/ArticleID2016112123625884.aspx|title=Consulate General of Saudi Arabia in Houston: Student Hussein Al-Nahdi Dies After Being Assaulted by an Unknown Person |work=[[The Consulate of the Kingdom of Saudi Arabia in Houston]]|date=2 November 2016 |accessdate=4 December 2016}}</ref>
