{{Infobox football biography | name = Paul Aeby | image = | caption = | fullname = | birth_date = {{birth date|1910|09|10|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Fribourg]], [[Switzerland]] | death_date = | height = | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 1936–1939| clubs1 = [[BSC Young Boys]]| caps1 = |goals1 = | years2 = 1939–1942| clubs2 = [[FC Grenchen]]| caps2 = |goals2 = | years3 = 1942–1947| clubs3 = [[FC Bern 1894]]| caps3 = |goals3 = | nationalyears1 = 1936–1946| nationalteam1 = [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] | nationalcaps1 = 20| nationalgoals1 = 4 }}
'''Paul Aeby''' (born 10 September 1910, date of death unknown) was a [[Swiss people|Swiss]] [[association football|footballer]] who played for [[Switzerland national football team|Switzerland]] in the [[1938 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>[http://pt.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/edition=5/teams/team=43971.html Seleção Suíça na Copa do Mundo FIFA de 1938] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120323121055/http://pt.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/edition%3D5/teams/team%3D43971.html |date=2012-03-23 }}</ref> He also played for [[BSC Young Boys]], [[FC Grenchen]], and [[FC Bern 1894]]. He was [[Georges Aeby]]'s elder brother.
